         <div type="notes">
            <note xml:id="n05080701" n="1">Almost certainly <name type="person" key="Labiche, François">Fran<seg n="u231">ç</seg>ois Labiche</name>. He is referred to again as "William" on <ref n="1804-08-18" type="related">August 18</ref> and <ref n="1804-08-19" type="related">19</ref>, 1804.</note>
            <note xml:id="n05080702" n="2">These must have been clear and specific orders to take <name type="person" key="Reed, Moses B.">Reed</name> dead or alive, made a matter of record so that the responsibility would fall on the captains, not on the men sent out.</note>
            <note xml:id="n05080703" n="3">This situation, in <name type="place" key="Harrison County, Iowa">Harrison County</name>, <name type="place" key="Iowa">Iowa</name>, was still present in altered form about 1890 but has since disappeared. <hi rend="italic">Atlas</hi> map 14; MRC map 25; MRR maps 69, 70.</note>
            <note xml:id="n05080704" n="4">
               <name type="person" key="Biddle, Nicholas">Biddle</name> apparently crossed out two lines of this entry in red, covering the words from "<name type="person" key="Reed, Moses B.">reid</name>" to "Death." In his <hi rend="italic">History,</hi>
               <name type="person" key="Biddle, Nicholas">Biddle</name> did not mention that the detachment had orders to kill <name type="person" key="Reed, Moses B.">Reed</name> if they could not take him alive. Probably the passage was crossed out because either <name type="person" key="Clark, William">Clark</name> or <name type="person" key="Biddle, Nicholas">Biddle</name> did not care to mention this aspect of the affair. Coues (HLC), 1:69.</note>
            <note xml:id="n05080705" n="5">Probably in northwest <name type="place" key="Harrison County, Iowa">Harrison County</name>, a few miles below the mouth of the <name type="place" key="Little Sioux (Ye-yeau War-da-pon) River">Little Sioux River</name>. <hi rend="italic">Atlas</hi> map 14; MRC map 25; MRR map 70.</note>
            <note xml:id="n05080706" n="6">
               <name type="person" key="Drouillard, George">Drouillard</name>, <name type="person" key="Field, Reubin">Reubin Field</name>, <name type="person" key="Bratton, William E.">William Bratton</name>, and <name type="person" key="Labiche, François">Fran<seg n="u231">ç</seg>ois Labiche</name> were sent to apprehend <name type="person" key="Reed, Moses B.">Reed</name>.</note>
